  "notes": [
    "Local Apple Silicon receipt only; does not claim GB10 parity.",
    "adam8bit (default) uses symmetric int8 blockwise quantization, matching the existing M0 codec. adam8bit_dynamic uses the bitsandbytes-style 256-entry signed dynamic LUT (denser bins near zero); both share the per-256-block uint8 + fp32-absmax memory layout so the state size is identical.",
